x4freetext: Statistical Model.
Review of another authors results.
The stacks used at Orsay contained 9 and 10 smaller
stacks each consisting of V, Co, Ti, Fe, Ni Foils and
Mn/Ni alloy. The foils had diameters of 20 mm and were
of the highest purities.
Each of target foils was followed by a 250 mu-m
high purity Al catcher foil.
The stacks used at Louvain La Neuve consisted out of 7
smaller stacks, containing the same elements as the
Orsay stacks. The foils had a diameter of 15.7 mm.

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: Centre d`Etudes Nucleaires, note, No.1466 (1975)

x4freetext: The uncertainties of the proton energies
consider both the thickness of the target foils and
the error introduced by the energy straggling.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The errors quoted for the cross sections
are absolute errors and consider all sources of errors
affecting the determination of cross sections (see
STUECK`s thesis, 1983).
Corrections of BIB- and Data-Sections have
been done.
Additional corrections for reaction lines
are included and author list is corrected.
Last checking has been done.
SD: DECAY-DATA corrected in several Subents
Small corrections in all Subents (SF9=EXP deleted;
SF6=SIG/UND -> SIG, in REACTION code etc.)
Independent
This cross section could be assumed as independent one,
because uncertainty of Sc-47 cross section is larger
than Ca-47 production cross section.
